    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-12T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/180: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-12T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 12, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 12—9:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>983. Acting upon your No. 360, November 2, I have named Jacobs and Bucknell as
                    delegates of the Legation for the negotiations in regard to the Provisional
                    Court.</p>
                <pb facs="0857" n="713" xml:id="pg_713"/>
                <p>2. I am preparing to send Bucknell November 14th to Shanghai for consultation
                    with Cunningham and Jacobs and request your approval therefor.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d709fn3">The Acting Secretary, in telegram No. 374, November 13,
                        replied, “Your action approved.” (893.05/180)</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
